Yugoslavia Wins First Match in Euro Soccer Qualifier
In another match of group eight , Macedonia won 2 - 1 in Malta to join Mick McCarthy 's side on six points in a three-way tie , along with Croatia , at the top of the pool .
Northern Ireland twice fought back to draw 2 - 2 with Moldova in Belfast but they really needed a win to stay in contention in a tough group three that also includes Turkey , Germany and surprise leaders Finland .
Greece failed to take top spot in group two as they were held to a 0 - 0 draw in Albania while Cyprus , who beat Spain in September , scraped a 1 - 0 away win over San Marino in group six .
Among the night 's three high-profile friendlies , two matches ended level as Italy and Spain drew 2 - 2 and Germany drew 1 - 1 with the Netherlands .
While in another friendly , England ended Czech Republic 's 10-match unbeaten run with a 2 - 0 win .
